Spec: Agent Skills Validator

Platform: Node.js

Purpose:
  Validate the generated Agent Skills standard distribution using documented Agent Skills constraints.

Owns:
  ./agentskills-validator.js

Must:
  Run without third-party dependencies or network access.
  Accept the generated package root path as its only command-line argument.
  Validate root-level `<skill-name>/SKILL.md` directories under the given distribution root.
  Require every skill directory name to match the Agent Skills `name` field constraints.
  Require each `SKILL.md` file to start with YAML frontmatter followed by Markdown content.
  Require `name` and `description` frontmatter fields.
  Require frontmatter `name` to match the skill directory name.
  Require `name` to be 1-64 characters, lowercase ASCII letters, numbers, and hyphens only, with no leading, trailing, or consecutive hyphen.
  Require `description` to be 1-1024 characters.
  Allow optional `license`, `compatibility`, `metadata`, and `allowed-tools` frontmatter fields.
  Require `compatibility` to be 1-500 characters when present.
  Require `metadata` to be a mapping when present.
  Print a concise validation summary on success.
  Print concrete file-specific failures and exit nonzero on validation failure.

Must not:
  Modify generated Agent Skills distribution output.
  Validate Codex, Claude, Copilot, Junie, Cline, or Antigravity package-specific rules.
